Script discourse part 2.

Everyone should stop making shitty jokes. People have told you to stop.
But I do want to add that poorly-scripted communication can hurt people with e.g. anxiety/depression/experiences of abuse. So I've made a couple of script improvement suggestions.

The key thing is that you should let the other person know what topic you're venting on. If you're too vague, someone with depression/anxiety/abuse trauma might start spiraling, which can trigger panic/etc.

That way, the other person is at less risk of feeling minimised or that they shouldn't have bothered somebody. Their situation has been acknowledged, which is in itself often an important thing. This is important if said person has been abused or has depression or anxiety.
